translation: Then gopis talking amongst themselves, said to Krishna, “We swear by Balram and Yashoda, please do not annoy us;

translation: “O Krishna! think in your mind, you will not gain anything in this; you hand over the clothes to us in water, we all shall bless you.”261.

transliteration: Pher Kahimoukh Te Im Gopin Baat Isimanue Pat Daihai|| Sauh Daro Mousleedhar Ki Jasudhaa Nand Kiham Jo Dahkai-ho||
translation: Then the gopis said to Krishna, “The love is not observed by force; the love that is created on seeing with eyes is the actual love.”

transliteration: Kaahn Kahihas(i) Kai Eh Baat Souno Ras Reet Kaho Mam Horee|| Ookhan Saath Lagad Takvaa Phoun Haathan Saath Lagad Soubh Soree||262||
translation: Krishna said smilingly, “See, do not make me understand the mode of amorous pastime; with the support of eyes, the love is then performed with hands.”262.

transliteration: Pher Kahimoukh Te Goupeeaa Hamre Pat Deh(u) Kahyo Nand Laalaa|| Pher(i) Shanaan Darain Na Ihaan Kah(i) Kai Ham Logad Aachhan Baalaa||
translation: The gopis said again, “O son of Nand! give us the clothes, we are good women; we will never come to have bath here.”

translation: Krishna replied, “Alright; come out of the water immediately and bow before me,” he added smilingly, “Be quick, I shall give you the clothes just now.”263

translation: All of them decided, “Alright, let us go out of water and then request Krishna.”264.

translation: All the them came out of water, concealing their secret parts with their hands; they fell at the feet of Krishna and requested him in various ways;
